INSERT INTO `intersectionality_tips` VALUES (8,'Gender','For SC Field Staff. Sourcebook on how to approach school reopening after COVID-19. For useful technical annexes, see Annex5 Participatory Education and Protection Continuity Planning.',1,72,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:32:45','2022-03-08 06:32:45'),(9,'COVID-19 and Disability','<p>For SC Project Managers. Useful for planning a coordinate response with communities, health providers, CBOs to guarantee protection for children with disabilities during COVID pandemics.</p>',1,73,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:33:24','2023-03-27 23:08:43'),(10,'Disability & stereotypes','<p>For School Heads, Teachers of ECCD, primary and secondary schools. Pedagogical approaches and activities to make the learning environment of the day care center welcoming, reliable, accessible, diverse, and safe to develop children with disabilities social skills and sphere.</p>',1,74,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:34:15','2023-03-27 23:09:30'),(11,'Sexual and Gender Based Violence','<p>For teachers and school staff. Training session to understand the role and responsibilities of schools and teachers in responding when a child has experienced sexual violence. It is vital that teachers know how to refer learners to appropriate care in all cases of distress and harm. <em><strong>Teachers are not equipped to provide clinical counselling or other types of specialized support.</strong></em></p>',3,75,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:35:49','2023-03-28 00:46:53'),(12,'Discrimination and  Stereotypes','<p>For teacher trainers, SC field staff, teachers. <a href=\"https://www.eenet.org.uk/the-10-videos-and-manuals/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Series of stand-alone sessions with suggested video and text</a>. See Program 1<a href=\"https://www.eenet.org.uk/the-10-videos-and-manuals/\"> &ndash; Activity 1.2. for training session on Discrimination and Stereotypes</a>.</p>',3,76,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:36:59','2023-03-28 00:49:15'),(13,'Ethnicity and religion','<p>For primary school students. Lesson about different hairstyles and identities.</p>',3,77,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:37:34','2023-03-28 00:45:24'),(14,'Social Identity  and Diversity','<p>For kindergarten and primary school children. Lesson about concepts of identity, diversity, group, respect.</p>',3,78,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:38:27','2023-03-28 00:50:12'),(15,'Gender and Gender  discrimination and  stereotypes','<p>For teachers and educators. Tools for activities and reflection that can also be used as a teacher training material. See pages 11-27 on how to make the classroom gender friendly.</p>',3,79,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:39:09','2023-03-28 00:50:51'),(16,'Physical characteristics','<p>For primary school students. Lessons to self-evaluate their own biases related to size differences.</p>',3,80,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:39:48','2023-03-28 00:51:12'),(17,'Ableism prejudice  and stereotypes','<p>For primary school students and USA teachers. Lesson aiming at developing students&rsquo; ability to recognize and challenge ableist discourse. Need for a country adaptation for all countries but the US (lesson material refers to popular US children&rsquo;s books).</p>',3,81,'en',1,1,1,'2022-03-08 06:40:32','2023-03-28 00:51:36'),(18,'Gender and disability','<p>Repository of toolkits and guidelines on inclusive education for girls with disabilities. See page 28, Programs and practices addressing barriers to education for girls with disabilities.</p>',8,86,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-03 08:07:43','2022-04-03 08:07:43'),(19,NULL,'<p>14 programming steps. See step 10 for vulnerable populations (including girls and women with disabilities), step 11 for MHM and Education, step 13 for MHM and Protection. Useful for: program staff, project managers, M&amp;E officers, technical staff. Available in two formats: The full guide and the mini guide (quick read). Not only for emergency settings.</p>',8,87,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-03 08:09:53','2022-04-11 09:26:01'),(20,'Disability and COVID-19','<p>Tool for SC Project Managers useful for planning integrate response to guarantee continuity in Education during COVID-19 pandemics</p>',8,88,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-03 08:10:59','2022-04-03 08:11:56'),(21,NULL,'<p>Tool for SC Project Managers useful for planning integrate response to guarantee quality WASH services provision during COVID-19 pandemics</p>',8,89,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-03 08:13:00','2022-04-18 07:54:07'),(22,NULL,'<p>Tool for SC Project Managers useful for planning integrate response to guarantee continuity in Health services provision during COVID-19 pandemics</p>',8,90,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-03 08:14:14','2022-04-18 07:54:27'),(23,NULL,'<p>Tool for SC Project Managers useful for planning integrate response to guarantee continuity in Nutrition services provision during COVID-19 pandemics</p>',8,91,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-03 08:14:52','2022-04-18 08:58:50'),(24,'Gender and COVID-19','<p>Guidance notes for Project Managers and implementers to make sure WASH programming and delivery is participative and inclusive through engagement of SGM communities and organizations</p>',8,92,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-03 08:15:53','2022-04-03 08:15:53'),(25,'Gender','<p>For teachers and teacher educators. A Guide for Strengthening Gender Equality and Inclusiveness in Teaching and Learning Materials: guidance on development and evaluation of materials to promote equality and inclusiveness of all marginalized, disadvantaged, and underrepresented groups.</p>',17,109,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-18 08:52:36','2022-04-18 08:52:36'),(26,NULL,'<p>For practitioners, teachers. A framework that outlines some of the factors that determine the quality of teaching of marginalized girls. It helps reflecting on working with marginalized girls and adapting teachers\' approaches to teacher professional development</p>',17,110,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-18 08:53:32','2022-04-18 08:53:32'),(27,NULL,'<p>A series of tools and practical guidance to help practitioners ensure education in emergency (EiE) interventions and programs are gender-responsive and inclusive. See page 151, 5.3 Gender in EiE Protection and Well-Being Interventions for a tool to understand the rationale for, and how to reflect, gender responsiveness in protection and well-being interventions within EiE programs.</p>',17,111,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-18 08:54:25','2022-04-18 08:54:25'),(28,'Discrimination and  Stereotypes','<p>For teachers. Classroom environment assessment to value: participation, health and well-being, safety and protection, enrollment and completion of studies, academic success, motivation of teachers, community support.</p>',17,112,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-18 08:55:25','2022-04-18 08:55:25'),(29,'Ethnicity and language','<p>For PM. Report and case studies from successful BC IEE projects addressing several issues, including Displaced Populations and Minority Ethnic Groups in the classroom.</p>',17,114,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-18 08:56:19','2022-04-18 08:56:19'),(30,'Physical characteristics  and access','<p>For individual schools. Self-reflection tool with questions designed to provide a picture of the environment&rsquo;s inclusiveness, focusing on its social, learning, and physical aspects.</p>',1,261,'en',0,1,1,'2022-04-18 08:57:07','2023-04-16 02:37:38'),(31,'Discrimination,  Stigmatization, and  Stereotypes','<p>For project managers.</p>\r\n<p>Nine SC case studies of successful Inclusive Education programs organized as follows: Background &ndash; Approach - Engagement of Stakeholders and Partners &ndash; Child Participation &ndash; Key Milestones &ndash; Significant Challenges &ndash; Scalability and Sustainability &ndash; Suggestions for further implementation &ndash; Case studies &ndash; References to SC Project Material and Contacts. See p.29, China on the successful inclusion of children with disabilities; p. 45, Kosovo on the inclusion of ethnic minorities in school.</p>',28,172,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-21 04:23:27','2023-03-30 02:33:44'),(32,'COVID-19 and Disability','<p>For school heads and teachers.</p>\r\n<p>Short document with useful tips for school heads and teachers training strategies to implement inclusive education for children with disabilities during COVID-19. Disabilities are not discussed in detail, but there are useful referrals to other documents.</p>',28,88,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-21 04:24:52','2023-03-30 02:34:12'),(33,'Lack of Psychological  Support for parents','<p>For teachers.</p>\r\n<p>The sourcebook at UNIT 5 provides the reader with good guidelines on how to work with parents and families and engage them in their children&rsquo;s education.</p>',28,173,'en',1,1,1,'2022-04-21 04:26:29','2023-03-30 02:35:11'),(34,'Gender','<p>For project managers.</p>\r\n<p>See page 61 for a guide with all necessary criteria to provide gender-responsive program strategies.</p>',33,70,'en',1,1,1,'2022-05-18 04:13:16','2022-07-06 08:57:01'),(35,'Physical characteristics  and Access','<p>For individual schools.</p>\r\n<p>Checklist to access school inclusiveness in the following domains:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; -&nbsp; teaching languages and methods</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; -&nbsp; pro-integration policies</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; -&nbsp; school environment</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; -&nbsp; student\'s well-being</p>',33,206,'en',1,1,1,'2022-05-18 04:19:38','2023-04-17 23:39:26'),(36,'Teachers’ Awareness  and Capacity building','<p>For teachers and school heads.</p>\r\n<p>Detailed manual on how to plan and organize the school for the inclusion of children with disabilities, covering a variety of aspects: access to information, school facilities and quality learning; inclusive planning; classroom management; tools for assessment of the level of inclusiveness; tools for assessment of children&rsquo;s learning difficulties.</p>',1,165,'en',1,1,1,'2022-05-18 04:30:10','2023-04-17 23:44:33'),(37,'Financial barriers','<p>For individual schools (that have not yet implemented inclusive education or are only beginning to do so).</p>\r\n<p>The strategies represented in the guide are structured using a multi-tiered approach and are meant to be applied in countries which lack the resources for implementing inclusive education (but can be equally applied in other contexts).</p>',33,190,'en',1,1,1,'2022-05-18 04:38:27','2022-07-06 08:58:38'),(38,'Gender & disability','<p>For INGOs, Project Managers, and Community Workers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>See page 98, 4.1 Gender in EiE advocacy and communications for a checklist for advocacy planning and delivery to understand and address the issue and the challenges of advocacy for gender-responsive education in acute emergencies.</p>',40,70,'en',1,1,1,'2022-06-13 06:30:49','2022-06-13 06:31:39'),(39,'Language','<p>Guidelines and Advocacy Strategies for trainers and educators to help ensure access to quality learning for English Language Learners</p>',40,268,'en',1,1,1,'2022-06-13 06:32:52','2023-04-01 23:35:03'),(40,'COVID 19','<p>For schools heads and teachers. Short document with useful tips and teacher training strategies with regards to disability inclusion during COVID-19 education. Disabilities are never discussed in detail. See the BEFORE SCHOOLS RE-OPEN &gt; Advocacy section.</p>',40,88,'en',1,1,1,'2022-06-13 06:34:31','2023-04-01 23:36:03'),(41,'Discrimination and  stereotypes','<p>For Policy Makers. Report and case studies from successful BC IE projects. See Minority Ethnic Groups in the classroom section.</p>',40,114,'en',1,1,1,'2022-06-13 06:35:48','2023-04-18 00:18:12'),(42,'Economic opportunities','<p>For Policy makers and stakeholders. Text sourcebook with bullet points on strategies to implement inclusive education in low-income countries.</p>',40,207,'en',1,1,1,'2022-06-13 06:36:55','2022-06-13 06:36:55'),(46,'Género','<p>Para personal de campo de SC. Libro de consulta sobre c&oacute;mo afrontar la reapertura de escuelas despu&eacute;s del COVID-19. Para anexos t&eacute;cnicos &uacute;tiles, v&eacute;ase el Anexo 5 Participatory Education and Protection Continuity Planning.</p>',191,236,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-02 06:39:58','2023-02-14 01:54:25'),(47,'COVID-19 y discapacidad','<p>Para gestores de proyectos de SC. &Uacute;til para planear una respuesta coordinada con comunidades, proveedores de salud y CBOs para garantizar la protecci&oacute;n de los ni&ntilde;os y ni&ntilde;as con discapacidad durante la pandemia de COVID.</p>',191,237,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-02 06:41:47','2023-02-14 01:54:43'),(48,'Discapacidad y estereotipos','<p>Para directores escolares. educadores de ECCD y docentes de escuelas de primaria y secundaria. Enfoques pedag&oacute;gicos y actividades para el ambiente de aprendizaje de educaci&oacute;n preescolar sea acogedor, fiable, accesible, diverso y seguro para el desarrollo de las habilidades sociales de los ni&ntilde;os y las ni&ntilde;as con discapacidad.</p>',191,238,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-02 06:42:28','2023-02-14 01:54:49'),(49,'Violencia sexual  y de género','<p>Para docentes y personal de las escuelas. Sesi&oacute;n de formaci&oacute;n para entender el papel y las responsabilidades de las escuelas y los docentes de dar respuesta cuando los ni&ntilde;os y las ni&ntilde;as experimentan violencia sexual. Es vital que los docentes sepan c&oacute;mo remitir a los estudiantes para que reciban el cuidado apropiado en cualquier caso de sufrimiento y da&ntilde;o.<strong> Los docentes no est&aacute;n formados para realizar atenci&oacute;n clinica u otros tipos de apoyo especializado. Los docentes no est&aacute;n formados para dar asesoramiento cl&iacute;nico ni otros tipos de apoyo</strong> <strong>especializado</strong>.</p>',193,75,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 03:19:30','2023-04-25 00:19:44'),(50,'Discriminación y estereotipos','<p>Para formadores de docentes, equipo de campo de SC, docentes. <a href=\"https://www.eenet.org.uk/the-10-videos-and-manuals/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Series of stand-alone sessions with suggested video and text</a>. V&eacute;ase el Programa <a href=\"https://www.eenet.org.uk/the-10-videos-and-manuals/programme-1-before-school/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">1 &ndash; Activity 1.2. for training session on Discrimination and Stereotypes</a>.</p>',193,241,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 03:25:46','2023-02-14 03:25:46'),(51,'Etnia y religión','<p>Para estudiantes de primaria. Lecci&oacute;n sobre los distintos peinados e identidades.</p>',193,242,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 03:30:20','2023-02-14 03:30:20'),(52,'Identidad social  y diversidad','<p>Para ni&ntilde;os y ni&ntilde;as de preescolar y primaria. Lecciones sobre conceptos de identidad, diversidad, grupo, respeto.</p>',193,78,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 03:48:47','2023-02-14 03:48:47'),(53,'Género y discriminación  de género y estereotipos','<p>Para docentes y educadores. Herramientas para actividades y reflexi&oacute;n que se puede utilizar como material l de formaci&oacute;n de docentes. V&eacute;anse las p&aacute;ginas 11 a 27 sobre c&oacute;mo hacer que el aula sea amigable con el g&eacute;nero.</p>',193,79,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 03:49:25','2023-02-14 03:49:25'),(54,'Características físicas','<p>Para estudiantes de primaria. Lecciones para autoevaluar sus propios sesgos relacionados con las diferencias de tama&ntilde;o.</p>',193,80,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 03:49:57','2023-02-14 03:49:57'),(55,'Prejuicio de capacitismo  y estereotipos','<p>Para estudiantes de primaria y docentes de EE.UU. Lecciones para desarrollar habilidades en los estudiantes para reconocer y enfrentar el discurso de capacitismo. Es necesario adaptarlo a todos los pa&iacute;ses excepto EE.UU. (el material de la lecci&oacute;n hace referencia a libros infantiles populares en EE.UU.)</p>',191,81,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 03:50:36','2023-04-25 00:24:21'),(56,'Género y discapacidad','<p>Repositorio de caja de herramientas y lineamientos sobre educaci&oacute;n inclusiva de ni&ntilde;as con discapacidades. V&eacute;ase p&aacute;gina 28. Programs and practices que abordan las barreras a la educaci&oacute;n de ni&ntilde;as con discapacidades.</p>',198,86,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 23:47:31','2023-02-14 23:47:31'),(57,NULL,'<p>14 pasos de programaci&oacute;n. V&eacute;ase el paso 10 para poblaciones vulnerables (incluyendo ni&ntilde;as y mujeres con discapacidad), paso 11 para MHM (gesti&oacute;n de la higiene menstrual) y educaci&oacute;n, paso 13 para MHM y protecci&oacute;n. &Uacute;til para: personal del programa, gesti&oacute;n de proyectos, responsables de M&amp;E (monitoreo y evaluaci&oacute;n), personal t&eacute;cnico. Disponible en dos formatos: Gu&iacute;a completa y mini gu&iacute;a (lectura r&aacute;pida). No solo para contextos de emergencia.</p>',198,87,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 23:50:52','2023-02-14 23:50:52'),(58,'Discapacidad y COVID-19','<p>Herramienta para gestores de proyectos de SC, &uacute;til para la planificaci&oacute;n de respuesta integrada para garantizar la continuidad de la educaci&oacute;n durante pandemias de COVID-19.</p>',198,88,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 23:52:03','2023-02-14 23:53:44'),(59,NULL,'<p>Herramienta para gestores de proyectos de SC, &uacute;til para la planificaci&oacute;n de respuesta integrada para garantizar servicios WASH de calidad durante pandemias de COVID-19.</p>',198,89,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 23:52:51','2023-02-14 23:52:51'),(60,NULL,'<p>Herramienta para gestores de proyectos de SC, &uacute;til para la planificaci&oacute;n de respuesta integrada para garantizar el suministro de servicios de salud durante pandemias de COVID-19.</p>',198,90,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 23:54:21','2023-02-14 23:54:21'),(61,NULL,'<p>Herramienta para gestores de proyectos de SC, &uacute;til para la planificaci&oacute;n de respuesta integrada para garantizar el suministro de servicios de nutrici&oacute;n durante pandemias de COVID-19.</p>',198,91,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 23:54:54','2023-02-14 23:54:54'),(62,'Género y COVID-19','<p>Notas orientadoras para que gestores de proyectos e implementadores aseguren que la programaci&oacute;n e implementaci&oacute;n WASH sea participativa e inclusiva mediante la inclusi&oacute;n de comunidades y organizaciones de SGM.</p>',198,92,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-14 23:56:26','2023-02-14 23:57:39'),(63,'Género','<p>Para docentes y educadores. Una gu&iacute;a para reforzar la igualdad de g&eacute;nero y la inclusi&oacute;n en los materiales de ense&ntilde;anza y aprendizaje: gu&iacute;a sobre desarrollo y evaluaci&oacute;n de materiales para promover la igualdad e inclusi&oacute;n de todos los grupos marginados, desfavorecidos y subrepresentados.</p>',210,109,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-15 03:46:52','2023-02-15 03:46:52'),(64,NULL,'<p>Para profesionales, docentes. Un marco de trabajo que resalta algunos de los factores que determinan la calidad de la ense&ntilde;anza de ni&ntilde;as marginadas. Ayuda a reflexionar sobre el trabajo con ni&ntilde;as marginadas y adaptar los enfoques docentes al desarrollo profesional docente.</p>',210,110,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-15 03:48:49','2023-02-15 03:48:49'),(65,NULL,'<p>Una serie de herramientas y gu&iacute;a pr&aacute;ctica que ayuda a los profesionales a asegurar que las intervenciones y programas de educaci&oacute;n educaci&oacute;n en emergencias (EiE) sean sensibles al g&eacute;nero e inclusivas. V&eacute;ase p&aacute;gina 151, 5,3. Gender in EiE Protection and Well-Being Interventions sobre una heramienta para entender el fundamento y c&oacute;mo reflejar, sensibilidad al g&eacute;nero en las intervenciones de protecci&oacute;n y bienestar dentro de los programas de EiE.</p>',210,70,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-15 03:49:23','2023-02-15 03:49:23'),(66,'Discriminación y  estereotipos','<p>Para docentes. Evaluaci&oacute;n del ambiente de aula para evaluar: participaci&oacute;n, salud y bienestar, seguridad y protecci&oacute;n, inscripci&oacute;n y conclusi&oacute;n de estudios, &eacute;xito acad&eacute;mico, motivaci&oacute;n de docentes, apoyo comunitario.</p>',210,112,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-15 03:50:14','2023-02-15 03:50:14'),(67,'Etnia e idioma','<p>Para gesti&oacute;n de proyectos. Reportes y estudios de casos de proyectos IEE BC exitosos que tratan distintos asuntos, incluyendo poblaciones desplazadas y grupos &eacute;tnicos minoritarios en el aula.</p>',210,114,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-15 03:50:46','2023-02-15 03:50:46'),(68,'Características  físicas y acceso','<p>Para escuelas individuales. Herramienta de autorreflexi&oacute;n con preguntas dise&ntilde;adas para proporcionar una imagen de la inclusi&oacute;n del ambiente, centr&aacute;ndose en aspectos sociales, de aprendizaje y f&iacute;sicos.</p>',210,49,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-15 03:51:37','2023-02-15 03:51:37'),(69,'Discriminación, estigmatización y estereotipos','<p>Para gestores de proyectos. 9 estudios de caso exitosos de programas de educaci&oacute;n inclusiva de SC organizados de la siguiente manera: Contexto - Enfoque -Participaci&oacute;n de actores releventes y socios- Participaci&oacute;n infantil - Hitos clave - Retos significativos - Adaptabilidad y sostenibilidad - Sugerencias para mayor implementaci&oacute;n - Estudios de casos - Referencias a material de proyectos de SC y contactos. V&eacute;ase p&aacute;gina 29 China sobre la inclusi&oacute;n con &eacute;xito de ni&ntilde;ez con discapacidades, p&aacute;gina 45 Kosovo sobre la inclusi&oacute;n de minor&iacute;as &eacute;tnicas en la escuela.</p>',221,172,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-19 23:19:43','2023-02-19 23:19:43'),(70,'COVID-19 y discapacidad','<p>Para direcci&oacute;n de colegios y docentes. Breve documento con consejos &uacute;tiles, estrategias de formaci&oacute;n de direcci&oacute;n de escuelas y docentes para que implementen la educaci&oacute;n inclusiva para ni&ntilde;os y ni&ntilde;as con discapacidades durante la COVID-19. Las discapacidades no se discuten en detalle, pero hay referencias &uacute;tiles a otros documentos.</p>',221,88,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-19 23:20:48','2023-02-19 23:20:48'),(71,'Falta de apoyo  psicológico para  los padres','<p>Para docentes. El libro de consulta en la UNIT 5 proporciona al lector una buena orientaci&oacute;n sobre c&oacute;mo trabajar con padres y familias e incluirlos en la educaci&oacute;n de ni&ntilde;os y ni&ntilde;as.</p>',221,55,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-19 23:21:38','2023-02-19 23:21:38'),(72,'Género','<p>Para directores de proyectos. V&eacute;ase p&aacute;gina 61 para una gu&iacute;a con todos los criterios necesarios para proporcionar estrategias de programas de respuesta al g&eacute;nero.</p>',229,70,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-20 01:50:27','2023-02-20 01:50:27'),(73,'Características  físicas y acceso','<p>Para escuelas individuales. Lista de verificaci&oacute;n para evaluar la inclusi&oacute;n escolar en las siguientes &aacute;reas:</p>\r\n<p>- ense&ntilde;ar idiomas y m&eacute;todos</p>\r\n<p>- pol&iacute;ticas de prointegraci&oacute;n</p>\r\n<p>- ambiente de la escuela&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- ambiente de la escuela&nbsp;</p>',229,44,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-20 01:51:24','2023-02-20 01:51:24'),(74,'Conciencia y  formación docente','<p>Para docentes y diretores de la escuela. Manual detallado sobre c&oacute;mo planear y organizar la escuela para la inclusi&oacute;n de ni&ntilde;os y ni&ntilde;as con discapacidades, cubriendo varios aspectos: acceso a la informaci&oacute;n; gesti&oacute;n de aula; herramientas para evaluar el nivel de inclusividad; herramientas para evaluar las dificultades de aprendizaje de los ni&ntilde;os y las ni&ntilde;as.</p>',229,165,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-20 01:52:08','2023-02-20 01:52:08'),(75,'Barreras Económicas','<p>Para escuelas individuales (que no hayan implementado a&uacute;n la educaci&oacute;n inclusiva o apenas empiezan a hacerlo). Las estrategias presentadas en la gu&iacute;a se estructuran usando un enfoque m&uacute;ltiple y su objetivo es que se usen en pa&iacute;ses con falta de recursos para implementar la educaci&oacute;n inclusiva(pero tambi&eacute;n se puede aplicar a otros contextos).</p>',229,190,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-20 01:52:48','2023-02-20 01:52:48'),(76,'Género y discapacidad','<p>Para ONGIs, directores de proyectos y trabajadores de la comunidad. V&eacute;ase p&aacute;gina 98, 4.</p>\r\n<p><em>1 Gender in EiE advocacy and communications</em> para una lista de verificaci&oacute;n de planificaci&oacute;n y entrega para entender y abordar el tema y los desaf&iacute;os de la defensa de una educaci&oacute;n sensible al g&eacute;nero en emergencias graves.</p>',239,70,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-20 03:58:16','2023-02-20 03:58:16'),(77,'Idioma','<p>Gu&iacute;as y estrategias de incidencia para formadores y educadores para ayudar a asegurar el acceso al aprendizaje de calidad para aprendices de ingl&eacute;s.</p>',239,44,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-20 04:03:34','2023-02-20 04:03:34'),(78,'COVID-19','<p>Para directores de escuelas y docentes. Breve documento con consejos &uacute;tiles y estrategias de formaci&oacute;n de docentes en relaci&oacute;n a la inclusi&oacute;n de la discapacidad en la educaci&oacute;n durante el COVID-19. Las discapacidades nunca se discuten en detalle. V&eacute;ase BEFORE SCHOOLS RE-OPEN &gt; Advocacy section.</p>',239,88,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-20 04:04:17','2023-02-20 04:04:17'),(79,'Discriminación y  estereotipos','<p>Para pol&iacute;ticos. Informe y estudios de casos para proyectos exitosos de EI del BC. V&eacute;ase la secci&oacute;n Minority Ethnic Groups in the classroom.</p>',239,114,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-20 04:05:11','2023-02-20 04:05:11'),(80,'Oportunidadeseconómicas','<p>Para pol&iacute;ticos y actores relevantes. Libro de consulta con puntos sobre estrategias para implementar la educaci&oacute;n inclusiva en pa&iacute;ses de bajos ingresos.</p>',239,207,'es',1,1,1,'2023-02-20 04:05:50','2023-02-20 04:05:50'),(81,'Genre','<p>Pour le personnel SC sur le terrain. Manuel sur la mani&egrave;re d\'aborder la r&eacute;ouverture des &eacute;coles apr&egrave;s la COVID-19. Sur des aspects techniques utiles, voir <em>Annex 5 Participatory Education and Protection Continuity Planning.</em></p>',243,72,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 00:34:24','2023-03-07 00:34:24'),(82,'COVID-19 et Handicap','<p>Pour les chefs de projet SC. Utile pour planifier une r&eacute;ponse coordonn&eacute;e avec les communaut&eacute;s, les prestataires de sant&eacute;, les organisations communautaires pour garantir la protection des enfants en situation de handicap pendant la pand&eacute;mie de COVID.</p>',243,73,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 00:35:07','2023-03-07 00:35:07'),(83,'Handicap et Stéréotypes','<p>Pour les directeurs d\'&eacute;cole, educateur de la Petite Enfance et les enseignants en primaire et secondaire. Approches et activit&eacute;s p&eacute;dagogiques visant &agrave; rendre l\'environnement d\'apprentissage accueillant, fiable, accessible, diversifi&eacute; et s&ucirc;r pour d&eacute;velopper les comp&eacute;tences sociales et le cadre des enfants en situation de handicap.</p>',243,74,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 00:35:55','2023-03-07 00:35:55'),(84,'Violence sexuelle et  basée sur le genre','<p>Pour les enseignants et le personnel scolaire. Session de formation pour comprendre le r&ocirc;le et les responsabilit&eacute;s des &eacute;coles et des enseignants dans la r&eacute;ponse &agrave; apporter lorsqu\'un enfant subit des violences sexuelles. Il est essentiel que les enseignants sachent comment les orienter vers des soins appropri&eacute;s en cas de d&eacute;tresse et pr&eacute;judice. <em><strong>Les enseignants ne sont pas aptes &agrave; fournir des conseils d\'ordre clinique ou d\'autres types de soutien sp&eacute;cialis&eacute;.</strong></em></p>',245,244,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 04:04:34','2023-03-07 04:04:34'),(85,'Discrimination et  Stéréotypes','<p>Pour les formateurs d\'enseignants, le personnel de terrain de SC, les enseignants. <a href=\"https://www.eenet.org.uk/the-10-videos-and-manuals/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Series of stand-alone sessions with suggested video and text</a>. Voir <a href=\"https://www.eenet.org.uk/the-10-videos-and-manuals/programme-1-before-school/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Program 1 &ndash; Activity 1.2. for training session on Discrimination and Stereotypes.</a></p>',245,76,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 04:10:17','2023-03-07 04:10:17'),(86,'Origine ethnique  et religion','<p>Pour les &eacute;l&egrave;ves de l\'&eacute;cole primaire. Le&ccedil;on sur les diff&eacute;rentes coiffures et identit&eacute;s.</p>',245,77,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 04:12:15','2023-03-07 04:12:15'),(87,'Identité sociale  et Diversité','<p>Pour les enfants de la maternelle et de primaire. Le&ccedil;on sur les concepts d\'identit&eacute;, de diversit&eacute;, de groupe, de respect.</p>',245,78,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 04:13:21','2023-03-07 04:13:21'),(88,'Genre et discrimination  basée sur le genre  et stéréotypes','<p>Pour les enseignants et les &eacute;ducateurs. Des outils d\'activit&eacute;s et de r&eacute;flexion pouvant &ecirc;tre aussi utilis&eacute;s comme mat&eacute;riel de formation des enseignants. Voir les pages 11 &agrave; 27 pour savoir comment faire pour qu\'une salle de classe soit am&eacute;nag&eacute;e de mani&egrave;re &agrave; respecter l\'&eacute;galit&eacute; des sexes.</p>',245,79,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 04:14:22','2023-03-07 04:14:22'),(89,'Caractéristiques  physiques','<p>Pour les &eacute;l&egrave;ves de l\'&eacute;cole primaire. Cours d\'auto-&eacute;valuation de leurs propres pr&eacute;jug&eacute;s vis-&agrave;-vis des diff&eacute;rences de taille.</p>',245,80,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 04:15:05','2023-03-07 04:15:05'),(90,'Préjugés et stéréotypes  liés au handicap','<p>Pour les &eacute;l&egrave;ves de l\'&eacute;cole primaire et les enseignants aux &Eacute;tats-Unis. Le&ccedil;on visant &agrave; d&eacute;velopper la capacit&eacute; des &eacute;l&egrave;ves &agrave; reconna&icirc;tre et &agrave; contester les pr&eacute;jug&eacute;s et st&eacute;r&eacute;otypes li&eacute;s au handicap. Adaptation n&eacute;cessaire pour tous les pays en dehors des &Eacute;tats-Unis (le mat&eacute;riel p&eacute;dagogique fait r&eacute;f&eacute;rence &agrave; des livres populaires pour les enfants aux &Eacute;tats-Unis).</p>',245,81,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-07 04:15:38','2023-03-07 04:16:05'),(94,'Genre et handicap','<p>R&eacute;f&eacute;rentiel de bo&icirc;tes &agrave; outils et de directives sur l\'&eacute;ducation inclusive pour les filles en situation de handicap. Voir page 28, Programs and practices addressing barriers to education for girls with disabilities.</p>',251,86,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-12 03:43:55','2023-03-12 03:43:55'),(95,NULL,'<p>14 &eacute;tapes sur la mise en place de programmes. Voir step 10 for vulnerable populations (including girls and women with disabilities), step 11 for MHM and Education, step 13 for MHM and Protection. Utile pour : le personnel des programmes, les gestionnaires de projets, les responsables du suivi et de l\'&eacute;valuation, le personnel technique. Disponible en deux formats : Le guide complet et le mini-guide (lecture rapide). Peut &ecirc;tre utilis&eacute; en dehors des situations d\'urgence.</p>',251,87,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-12 03:44:28','2023-03-12 03:44:28'),(96,'Handicap et COVID-19','<p>Outil pour les gestionnaires de projet de SC utile pour planifier une r&eacute;ponse int&eacute;gr&eacute;e visant &agrave; garantir la continuit&eacute; de l\'&eacute;ducation pendant la pand&eacute;mie de COVID-19.</p>',251,88,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-12 03:45:20','2023-03-12 03:45:20'),(97,NULL,'<p>Outil pour les gestionnaires de projet de SC utile pour planifier une r&eacute;ponse int&eacute;gr&eacute;e visant &agrave; garantir la qualit&eacute; li&eacute;e au WASH pendant la pand&eacute;mie de COVID-19</p>',251,89,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-12 04:11:51','2023-03-12 04:15:12'),(99,NULL,'<p>Outil pour les gestionnaires de projet de SC utile pour planifier une r&eacute;ponse int&eacute;gr&eacute;e visant &agrave; garantir la continuit&eacute; des services de sant&eacute; pendant la pand&eacute;mie de COVID-19.</p>',251,90,'fr',1,1,1,'2023-03-12 04:13:44','2023-03-12 04:13:44'),(100,NULL,'<p>Outil pour les gestionnaires de projet de SC utile pour planifier une r&eacute;ponse int&eacute;gr&eacute;e visant &agrave; garantir la continuit&eacute; des serv